  "steps": [
    {
      "id": "l4-parents",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Parents and siblings",
      "body": "# Family members\n\nThe closest family words in English:\n\n- **Mother** (माँ) and **Father** (पिता) — your parents\n- **Brother** (भाई) and **Sister** (बहन) — your siblings\n- **Son** (बेटा) and **Daughter** (बेटी) — your children\n\nUnlike Hindi, English uses **one** word for *brother* whether older or younger — there is no separate word for बड़ा भाई or छोटा भाई. The same is true for *sister*, *uncle*, and *aunt*."
    },
    {
      "id": "l4-ex-match-close",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Match the family words",
      "exercise": {
        "id": "l4-ex-match-close",
        "type": "matching",
        "prompt": "Match each English family word with its Hindi meaning.",
        "card_ids": [
          "hi-mother",
          "hi-father",
          "hi-brother",
          "hi-sister"
        ],
        "pairs": [
          {
            "left": "Mother",
            "right": "माँ"
          },
          {
            "left": "Father",
            "right": "पिता"
          },
          {
            "left": "Brother",
            "right": "भाई"
          },
          {
            "left": "Sister",
            "right": "बहन"
          }
        ],
        "direction": "target_to_source"
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l4-ex-free-sister",
      "type": "exercise",
      "title": "Translate the word",
      "exercise": {
