              "Son"
            ]
          }
        ],
        "cloze_mode": "type",
        "hint": "A male child."
      }
    },
    {
      "id": "l4-extended",
      "type": "theory",
      "title": "Grandparents and spouses",
      "body": "# More relations\n\nBeyond the immediate family:\n\n| English | Hindi |\n|---|---|\n| Grandfather | दादा |\n| Grandmother | दादी |\n| Husband | पति |\n| Wife | पत्नी |\n| Friend | दोस्त |\n\nIn English we say **my** before the word: *my mother* (मेरी माँ), *my friend* (मेरा दोस्त). The word **my** does not change for gender — it is always *my*."
    },
